vagrant@u16vag:~$ docker -v
Docker version 17.03.0-ce, build 3a232c8

Now we absolutely want to run docker non-root user. In this test case, vagrant user.
vagrant@u16vag:~$ cat /etc/group | grep docker
docker:x:999:
vagrant@u16vag:~$ sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
vagrant@u16vag:~$ echo $USER
vagrant
vagrant@u16vag:~$ cat /etc/group | grep docker
docker:x:999:vagrant

!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!IMPORTANT!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Because I am going to run docker user(not root), I need to reboot virtualbox(vagrant) machine.
If you are not using virtualbox, just logout relogin would be better choice.(https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/linux-postinstall/#manage-docker-as-a-non-root-user)


